thread.title: LOCAL COLLEGES: Redlands wins in men's soccer

author: The Press-Enterprise
title: LOCAL COLLEGES: Redlands wins in men's soccer
text:
News service reports
 Updated: 10:49 p.m. The University of Redlands men’s soccer team defeated Claremont-Mudd-Scripps, 2-0, in a Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference game on Monday night.
The Bulldogs (10-2-2, 8-2-1) were ahead, 1-0, at halftime thanks to an unassisted goal in the 20th minute from Jesus Avalos. Kayvon Parsa scored the insurance goal on an assist by Chase Boone in the 56th minute.
MEN’S GOLF
Sonoma State Invite: CSUSB is in eighth place with a 594 after two rounds at Foxtail Golf Club in Rohnert Park. The Coyotes are led by Taylor Hood (146), who is tied for 16th.
